content.description: This job is responsible for reading data from the Metal staging layer and loading it into the Bronze SCD Type 2 tables. It ensures historical tracking of changes by identifying new, changed, and unchanged records, applying the appropriate logic to insert new versions or retire old ones with end dates as part of the SCD2 process.
content.name: cdi_adm_commission_preview_bronze_load

transformations.description: This source is designed to capture daily updates from the metal table and join with the target table to ensure that duplicate records are not loaded.
transformations.name: src_delta_changes_agency

object.customQuery:
WITH current_batch
     AS (SELECT bls.batch_id,
                bls.source_start_cutoff_datetime,
                bls.source_end_cutoff_datetime
         FROM   metal.batch_load_summary bls
         WHERE  bls.source_system_code = 'ADM'
                AND bls.batch_status = 'Inprogress'
                AND bls.batch_id = (SELECT Max(batch_id)
                                    FROM   metal.batch_load_summary
                                    WHERE  source_system_code = 'ADM'
                                           AND batch_status = 'Inprogress'))
SELECT DISTINCT metal_comm_preview.source_name,
                metal_comm_preview.load_type,
                metal_comm_preview.agency_nup,
                metal_comm_preview.created,
                metal_comm_preview.id,
                metal_comm_preview.modified,
                metal_comm_preview.state_company,
                metal_comm_preview.state_company_eff_date,
                metal_comm_preview.transferstatus,
                current_batch.batch_id
FROM   metal.adm_commission_preview metal_comm_preview
       CROSS JOIN current_batch
ORDER  BY metal_comm_preview.agency_nup,
          metal_comm_preview.id,
          metal_comm_preview.created,
          metal_comm_preview.modified

transformations.description: This source retrieves the most recent records (row_number = 1) from the target table to identify and retire the corresponding entries
transformations.name: src_tgt_query

object.customQuery:
SELECT commission_preview_row_id,
       commission_preview_batch_id,
       commission_preview_row_md5checksum,
       commission_preview_row_effective_end_datetime,
       agency_id,
       commission_preview_id
FROM   bronze.adm_commission_preview
WHERE  commission_preview_row_effective_end_datetime = '9999-12-31 00:00:00.000'

transformations.description: This expression transformation is used to calculate the MD5 form the output of the previous expression field's
transformations.name: exp_MD5_calculation

fields.name: o_src_MD5_hash_value
fields.expression:
MD5(
    'source_name' || source_name ||
    'load_type' || load_type ||
    'agency_nup' || to_char(o_agency_id) ||
    'created' || to_char(o_commisson_date_created) ||
    'id' || to_char(o_commisson_preview_id) ||
    'modified' || to_char(o_commisson_date_modified) ||
    'state_company' || state_company ||'state_company_eff_date'||to_char(o_state_company_eff_date) ||
    'transferstatus' || transferstatus )
